  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": true,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.1,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "Let's design a program with object"
      },
      {
        "start": 2.3,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "composition. We're building a real"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.0,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "estate marketplace where agents list"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.4,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "properties for sale. The listing for"
      },
      {
        "start": 9.8,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "each property tells us what kind of home"
      },
      {
        "start": 12.2,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "it is, its asking price, and then"
      },
      {
        "start": 14.7,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "information about its individual rooms."
      },
      {
        "start": 18.0,
        "duration": 7.0,
        "text": "In our class design, then we might say"
      },
      {
        "start": 20.5,
        "duration": 6.8,
        "text": "that a property has a list of rooms."
      },
      {
        "start": 25.0,
        "duration": 5.2,
        "text": "Each room keeps track of its own"
      },
      {
        "start": 27.3,
        "duration": 5.5,
        "text": "information like its kind, its square"
      },
      {
        "start": 30.2,
        "duration": 6.3,
        "text": "footage, and its level."
      },
      {
        "start": 32.8,
        "duration": 6.6,
        "text": "The property can then use its rooms to"
      },
      {
        "start": 36.5,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "calculate stats that buyers care about"
      },
      {
        "start": 39.4,
        "duration": 5.2,
        "text": "like the total square footage or the"
      },
      {
        "start": 41.5,
        "duration": 4.9,
        "text": "number of bedrooms."
      },
      {
        "start": 44.6,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "Let's start by modeling those two"
      },
      {
        "start": 46.4,
        "duration": 6.6,
        "text": "classes, a property and a room. We said"
      },
      {
        "start": 49.6,
        "duration": 6.2,
        "text": "a room has three attributes, a kind, a"
      },
      {
        "start": 53.0,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "level, and the number of square feet."
      },
      {
        "start": 55.8,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "Pretty straightforward. And we'll just"
      },
      {
        "start": 58.0,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "add a quick string method so we can"
      },
      {
        "start": 60.0,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "display a room nicely."
      },
      {
        "start": 63.8,
        "duration": 4.8,
        "text": "To test that, let's go back to main and"
      },
      {
        "start": 65.8,
        "duration": 6.2,
        "text": "create a room object. For example, we"
      },
      {
        "start": 68.6,
        "duration": 6.4,
        "text": "might have a kitchen on level two that's"
      },
      {
        "start": 72.0,
        "duration": 5.0,
        "text": "160 square ft."
      },
      {
        "start": 75.0,
        "duration": 5.7,
        "text": "And if we print that room, we'll get our"
      },
      {
        "start": 77.0,
        "duration": 6.5,
        "text": "nice string representation."
      },
      {
        "start": 80.7,
        "duration": 6.1,
        "text": "Cool. Time for the composition piece."
      },
      {
        "start": 83.5,
        "duration": 6.4,
        "text": "Let's define our property class. Like"
      },
      {
        "start": 86.8,
        "duration": 7.3,
        "text": "our outline said, a property has a kind,"
      },
      {
        "start": 89.9,
        "duration": 7.0,
        "text": "a price, and a list of rooms. We might"
      },
      {
        "start": 94.1,
        "duration": 5.7,
        "text": "say that a property owns a room because"
      },
      {
        "start": 97.0,
        "duration": 4.5,
        "text": "a specific room can't belong to multiple"
      },
      {
        "start": 99.8,
        "duration": 5.1,
        "text": "properties. That doesn't really make"
      },
      {
        "start": 101.4,
        "duration": 6.6,
        "text": "sense. And a property's rooms very"
      },
      {
        "start": 104.9,
        "duration": 5.8,
        "text": "rarely change over time."
      },
      {
        "start": 108.1,
        "duration": 5.6,
        "text": "But a property can have 10 rooms, 20"
